Description:

A new configuration file directive to include another file, but only if it exists. That is, if it's missing, it would not result in hard error. 
This is especially useful, to have "#include my_sip_users.d/*.conf" or similar to work properly even if the directory is empty.

It implements new "#-include".

This patch is based on an already existent patch for asterisk version 10.0.0
Link to original patch: https://issues.asterisk.org/jira/browse/ASTERISK-19107

 1. Get the source for Asterisk 1.8.3.2 from:
 
 http://downloads.asterisk.org/pub/telephony/asterisk/old-releases/asterisk-1.8.3.2.tar.gz
 
 
 2. Untar the Asterisk 1.8.3.2
 
 $ tar -zxvf asterisk-1.8.3.2.tar.gz
 
 
 3. Add the app WMS to asterisk
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-app-wms.patch
 
 
 4. Add the codec AMR
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-codec-amr.patch
 
 
 5. Add the SMRA support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-smra-support.patch


 6. Add the feature reject mode
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-reject-mode.patch 
 
 
 7. Add the multiple IP support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-udp-rtp-address-support.patch 


 8. Add the private extensions support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-private-extension.patch 

 
 9. Add the dtmf flash support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-dtmf-flash-support.patch 

 
 10. Add the extension tel support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-tel-extension.patch 


 11. Add minor changes
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-minor-changes.patch  
 
 
 12. Add ISUP support
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-chan-sip-isup.patch  
 
 13. Add warning suppress fix
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-warning-suppress-fix.patch  
 
 14. Add include if exists fix
 
 $ patch -p1 -d asterisk-1.8.3.2/ < asterisk-i-include-if-exists.patch 
 
 5. Build Asterisk
 
 $ cd asterisk-1.8.3.2
 $ ./configure
 $ make